lloyd bentsen said he thought he did fine 
in wednesday nights vice presidential debate and that republican 
opponent dan quayle did not adequately explain what he would do if 
he suddenly became president 
bentsen received a telephone call from democratic presidential 
nominee michael dukakis immediately after the debate then left for 
a rally at a nearby hotel 
there the democratic vice presidential nominee was cheered by 
700 supporters a large sign declared and the winner is 
bentsen 
asked if he thought he had won the debate bentsen said i 
think i did fine and i enjoyed it i had fun i think we made our 
points 
bentsen referred to the repeated questioning of quayle about the 
republican vice presidential nominees qualifications to assume the 
presidency 
i stood up there for 90 minutes listening to senator quayle 
say what he was going to do if he was president of the united 
states and i still didnt know finally i realized all he was 
going to do was go back to that script again bentsen said 
dukakis called bentsen to wish him well before the debate the 
democratic ticket planned a reunion thursday at a steel plant rally 
near longview texas 
bentsen arrived in omaha on tuesday night after four days of 
intense preparations first in washington and then in austin 
texas he took time to spend with his wife and three children and 
planned to work out in the hotel gym to help him relax before the 
debate 
ba bentsen accompanied her husband to the private tour of the 
debate site wednesday afternoon afterward according to press 
secretary mike mccurry bentsen 67 picked up his wife and carried 
her off the stage she looked like she was willing to go with him 
anywhere he said 
much of his preparation was devoted to making bentsen 
comfortable with the format of the debate which limited the 
candidates to twominute answers and oneminute responses aides 
said 
its a matter of taking the language of the us senate and 
putting it in a form thats suitable for television mccurry said 
although his advisers admitted helping bentsen frame his 
answers mccurry said we have not armed him with a lot of cute 
oneliners thats not really his style 
i think well leave the oneliners to roger ailes and dan 
quayle said dukakis aide leslie dach referring to the 
republican media strategist who has been coaching the gop candidate 
bentsen and other democrats have tried to exploit public 
uneasiness about quayles qualifications for the job and public 
polls show quayle is a drag on the republican ticket a strong 
performance by the 41yearold quayle could turn that around 
i dont think people are going to judge this just by the fact 
he doesnt stumble dach said he said quayle needed an 
extremely strong performance to overcome the publics doubts 
