question why do you think that you have not made a more 
substantial impression on some of these people who have been able 
to observe you up close 
quayle qualifications for the office of vice president or 
president are not age alone lets look at the three biggest 
issues that are going to be confronting america in the next 
presidency those three issues are national security and arms 
control jobs and education and the federal budget deficit on 
each one of those issues i have more experience than does the 
governor of massachusetts 
bentsen this debate tonight is not about the qualifications 
for the vice presidency no the debate tonight is a debate about 
the presidency itself and a presidential decision that has to be 
made by you the stakes could not be higher 
question if you had to step in to the presidency whos agenda 
would you pursue yours or dukakis 
bentsen we agree on so many things and the vast majority 
of the issues we agree on the fact that we have to cut this 
deficit governor dukakis and i agree that we ought to have a 
trade policy for this country that weve seen this administration 
more than double the national debt that theyve moved this country 
from the no 1 lender nation in the world to the no 1 debtor 
nation in the world under their administration that they have not 
had a trade policy that theyve let trade be a handmaiden for the 
foreign policy objectives of the country that this country has 
exported too many jobs and not enough products 
quayle governor dukakis one of the most liberal governors 
in the united states of america raised taxes five times he 
just raised taxes this last year and thats why a lot of people 
refer to him tax hike mike thats why they refer to the state 
of massachusetts as taxachusetts 
question arent you and gov dukakis using social 
security politically rather than dealing with it responsibily 
bentsen we have a contract with the american people on 
social security and social security is an issue where sen quayle 
voted eight times to cut the benefits on social security now 
when you talk about social security the people that are going to 
protect it are the democrats who brought forth that program 
quayle sen bentsen you know that i did not vote to cut social 
security benefits eight times what i have voted for and what sen 
bentsen has voted for is to delay the costofliving adjustments 
youre right they use this for political advantage what they 
try to do time and time again is to scare the old people of this 
country 
question do you consider yourself an environmentalist and 
if you do how do you reconcile that with your voting record 
quayle i have a very strong record on the environment in the 
united states senate i have voted for the major pieces of 
environmental legislation that have come down and been voted on in 
the united states senate if you bring up the environment you 
cant help but think about the environmental policy of the governor 
of massachsetts the boston harbor which is the dirtiest 
waterway in america what has the governor of massachusetts 
done about that virtually nothing 
bentsen were the authors the democratic party of clean 
air of clean water of the superfunding im one who played a very 
major role in passing the superfund legislation and every 
environmental organization that i know every major one has now 
endorsed the dukakisbentsen ticket 
question id like for you to explain your votes against 
the school breakfast program the school lunch program and the 
expansion of the child immunization program 
quayle i have a very good record and a commitment to the 
poor to those that dont have a family want to have a family 
this administration and a george bush administration will be 
committed to eradicating poverty the poverty program we are 
going to concentrate on is creating jobs and opportunities so that 
everyone will have the opportunities that they want 
bentsen what also frustrates me is the kind of votes 
hes cast against child nutrition programs the fact that he has 
voted against money that we needed for further immunization the 
denial of polio shots to kids where the parents couldnt afford to 
get that kind of a shot now i dont really believe that is 
identifying with the concerns of people in poverty 
question you and michael dukakis seem to be diametrically 
opposed on contra aid 
bentsen gov dukakis and i have disagreed on the contra program 
but my big difference with this administration is they look at 
the contra aid program as the only way to resolve that problem 
i believe that you have to work with the leaders of those other 
central american countries to try to bring about the 
democratization of nicaragua 
quayle theres no doubt in a dukakis administration that the 
aid would be cut off to the democratic resistance in nicaragua and 
that is unfortunate 
question governor dukakis has tried to make ethics a major 
issue in the campaign and he has you as a running mate a man who 
leads the league at last count in the receipt of pac money do 
you find that embarrassing senator 
bentsen no i dont wwhat ive done in pac money is just 
what my opponent in my campaign has done in his campaign so 
what you have to do is comply with the laws as they are i have 
been for campaign reform and have pushed it very hard but ive 
noticed that the senator from indiana has opposed that campaign 
reform and voted repeatedly against it 
quayle senator bentsen is the number one pac raiser as a 
matter of fact he used to have a 10000 breakfast club it 
only cost highpaid lobbyist special interests in washington to 
come down and have breakfast with the chairman of the senate 
finance committe the one that oversees all the tax loopholes in 
the tax code 10000 im sure they werent paying to have corn 
flakes 
