<TEXT>
brazil today is to enact a new 
constitution consolidating the countrys return to democratic 
government after 21 years of rightwing military rule 
this is a historic date for our country president jose 
sarney told brazilians tuesday night in a nationwide tv broadcast 
we have reached the end of a long path my mission of helping 
the country through its transition to democracy is fulfilled 
the 559 legislators doubling as a constituent assembly worked 
for 19 months on the 245article document that governs everything 
from interest rates to mining rights and land reform the charter 
is brazils eighth since independence from portugal in 1822 and 
replaces the authoritarian document handed down by military 
generals in 1969 
the new constitution will consolidate a representative and 
participatory democracy the president of the constituent 
assembly rep ulysses guimaraes said in a press conference for 
the first time the individual will have precedence over the state 
sarney who at times fought bitterly against leftleaning 
measures in the new document said in his broadcast he would be the 
constitutions greatest servant 
in earlier broadcasts sarney made veiled threats that if 
certain articles were passed the military might refuse to respect 
the new constitution 
the constitution removes many of the arbitrary powers used by 
the military government during its harsh rule the document 
abolishes the presidents power to simply decree laws ends 
censorship prohibits torture guarantees political rights and 
broadens workers right to strike and to unionize 
nationalistic legislators also managed to limit mineral mining 
to national companies and prohibit further oil drilling risk 
contracts between the staterun petrobras which has a monopoly on 
oil exploration and drilling in brazil and international companies 
at the same time the rightwing scored a victory managing to 
waterdown a land reform law that protects productive land from 
expropriation the law further stalls sarneys program to 
distribute land to 14 million peasant families in a country where 
2 percent of landowners hold 60 pecent of arable land 
judiciary analysts have said however there are many articles 
in the hefty document that will be difficult to define or to 
enforce in complimentary legislation 
guimaraes 72 said the charter would be respected by all 
including the armed forces 
the military period left deep marks there is an awareness 
that the regime is good and from the armed forces we have heard 
only words of support and confidence in the stability of 
democracy guimaraes said 
the enactment of the new constituion will be marked by daylong 
celebrations starting early today with an openair mass before the 
twindomed congress and a reception for delegates from more than 30 
latin american and portuguesespeaking nations 
sarney 58 became president in 1985 after presidentelect 
tancredo neves died before taking office 
