the oklahoma native whose career spanned nearly 50 years shot 
more than 100 films ranging from such serious efforts as the 
caretakers for which he was nominated for an academy award to 
tworeel comedies starring the three stooges 
one of hollywoods most distinguished cameramen he worked with 
such directors as sam peckinpah stanley kubrick henry hathaway 
dorothy arzner and josef von sternberg 
but despite an illustrious career ballard never received the 
industrys top honor the academy award although nominated for 
the caretakers in 1963 he lost to james wong howe for hud 
two of his most renowned westerns peckinpahs the wild 
bunch and hathaways true grit were both filmed in 1969 
some in hollywood believed they may have canceled each other out in 
the oscar race for best cinematography that year true grit 
garnered a best actor oscar for john wayne 
ballard was planning to go into the lumber business when he 
discovered moviemaking after a script girl he was dating took him 
to a threeday party whose host was actress clara bow 
soon thereafter he visited paramount studios landing a job as a 
film cutter 
he gained von sternbergs attention while working as an 
assistant camera operator and the director used him on his 1930 
film morocco starring marlene dietrich ballard also worked 
with von sternberg on the devil is a woman and crime and 
punishment 
