in todays editions of the washington post 
the language of the findings seemingly was ambiguous the post 
said actions taken in good faith and as part of an approved 
operation would be deemed lawful in advance but also they must 
be lawful sources told the post 
the newspaper quoted a former white house official whom it did 
not identify as saying the reagan orders were a goanywhere 
doanything authority 
the language of the findings caused disputes among 
administration officials the post said because actions that could 
be authorized under the findings might conflict with earlier 
presidential executive orders banning any direct or indirect 
involvement of us intelligence agents in assassinations 
the post quoted a source as saying the language was specifically 
designed to circumvent the assassination ban and protect cia 
agents who might take part in foreign strike teams 
white house spokesman bob hall told the associated press he knew 
nothing about the findings late tuesday night 
the post reported that unidentified white house officials said 
vice president george bush would have been given a copy of or would 
have had access to the findings 
a bush spokesman and bush campaign chairman james baker iii who 
was white house chief of staff at the time reagan signed the 1984 
finding had no comment the post said 
reagan signed the first finding on nov 13 1984 shortly after 
his landslide reelection victory the report said because us 
officials had become frustrated with carbombings at us 
facilities and the taking of american hostages 
congressional intelligence committees were not informed of the 
crucial language in the findings the report said 
the authorization was rescinded on april 10 1985 a month after 
a car bomb exploded killing 80 people in beirut near the residence 
of a leader of one faction of iranian fundamentalists 
the second authorization which included similar language was 
signed by reagan on aug 11 1985 two months after the highjacking 
of twa flight 847 in which american navy diver robert stethem was 
killed the intelligence panels were briefed after the signing of 
the second finding the post said 
</TEXT>
