<TEXT>
dr george hatem an american physician who 
devoted his medical career to eradicating venereal diseases in the 
peoples republic of china has died in beijing state university 
officials said 
hatem 78 who died sunday had been hospitalized since aug 4 
he had been diagnosed as having cancer and diabetes 
once called the most beloved american in china he is widely 
credited with ridding the worlds most populous nation of most 
syphilis and gonorrhea and he had hoped to eliminate leprosy from 
the country by the year 2000 
in mainland china he was known as dr ma haiteh meaning 
virtue from overseas during the 1950s he became the first 
foreigner to become a chinese citizen 
officials at the state university of new york at buffalo said a 
cousin of hatems who had received a cable from the doctors 
widow informed them of his death 
dr steven b sample president of the university presented 
hatem an honorary doctor of science degree last year in beijing 
over the past halfcentury he led the fight against dreadful 
diseases like cholera venereal disease and leprosy in china and in 
the process saved the lives of many millions of chinese sample 
said 
the son of lebanese immigrants shafick hatem his first name 
was americanized to george grew up in buffalo 
his medical career may have had its roots in an influenza 
epidemic in 1918 when his entire family was stricken he recalled 
later how his family received care from a kindly doctor who made 
house calls and accepted no payment 
with an undergraduate degree from the university of north 
carolina hatem started his medical studies at the american 
university in beirut and received his medical degree from the 
university of geneva in switzerland in 1933 he and two other 
doctors went to shanghai to study tropical diseases hatem never 
came back 
shortly after his arrival in china hatem became friends with 
journalist edgar snow when mao tsetung became head of the 
communist party he sent word to shanghai that he wanted a 
westerntrained doctor and an honest journalist snow and hatem 
managed to get through the nationalist army lines to the 
communists where they first met chou enlai then mao 
hatem returned to shanghai when the red army took over china in 
1949 
as chief of staff of the chinese institute of dermatology and 
venereology he set up a patriotic health movement his first 
targets were acute communicable diseases such as cholera and 
smallpox 
the next battle against venereal diseases involved going to 
brothels treating the infected prostitutes and shutting down the 
brothels within 48 hours the women were retrained in other jobs 
hatem is survived by his wife ssufei a son a daughter a 
sister and two grandchildren 
</TEXT>
