<TEXT>
a dormitory for women workers has a ghost that 
steals boots and plays knockknock with some of the residents 
a newspaper reported wednesday 
the labor daily trud said the ghost was discovered three weeks 
ago by three young housepainters who live in the moscow dormitory 
it said they had learned to communicate with the specter by a 
code system of knocks one for yes and two for no 
when two trud reporters visited the dormitory the specter had 
stolen a boot according to the papers account the women asked 
several questions and got one knock for yes after asking whether 
the boot was behind a shelf 
trud said the painters became aware of the ghost in 
midseptember when it knocked loudly on a door and began making the 
door open and close one night 
although specialists are in no hurry to pronounce themselves 
definitively it seems more and more likely that in these and 
several other similar situations what is occuring is a rare natural 
phenomenon a poltergeist the report said 
a poltergeist is defined as a noisy and usually mischievous 
ghost held responsible for unexplained noises such as rappings 
although soviet society is officially materialist there is 
enormous interest here in flying saucers the bermuda triangle 
ghosts extrasensory perception and such real or imaginary monsters 
as the abominable snowman 
even the staid soviet academy of sciences has a commission on 
abnormal phenomena 
trud asked commission chairman v troitsky to comment on the 
dormitory ghost and quoted him as replying in our country the 
principle is still current that these things cant happen because 
they could never happen 
