uncalled for he said 
it was the second time this week that the high court ruled 
against the late military strongman zia and several of his top 
generals were killed in a plane crash on aug 17 
the supreme court ruled sunday in favor of a petition by ms 
bhutto challenging zias july decree that the elections in november 
be on a nonparty basis the court said the constitution guaranteed 
that candidates could run on party tickets rather than as 
individuals under zias plan 
the last democratic elections held in 1973 swept ms bhuttos 
father zulfikar ali bhutto into power as pakistans first 
popularly elected prime minister 
bhutto was deposed by zia in a military coup in 1977 zia had 
him hanged two years later 
zia ruled under martial law until 1985 when he allowed 
elections on a nonparty basis the opposition boycotted the voting 
and candidates favoring the prozia muslim league swept the 
elections 
zia shared power with the junejo government for three years 
