us rep robert dornan said his wifes 
mistaken public statement that her brother suffered from aids was 
prompted by worry and imagination according to a newspaper report 
published wednesday 
dornan and his wife sallie are very relieved and obviously 
extremely happy that her estranged brother doug hansen doesnt 
have the disease dornan told the orange county register in an 
interview 
the comments from dornan a republican who has been critical of 
the gay lifestyle apparently did little to end an unusual and 
highly public family feud 
at a public meeting sept 18 mrs dornan vividly described the 
plight of a brother dying of aids as she was apologizing for 
shouting shut up fag to a gay activist in the crowd asked 
who the brother was she said dougie 
dornan criticized his brotherinlaw a 51yearold landscape 
architect from san diego for discussing the matter with the news 
media 
hansen in interviews denied that he is gay and that he suffered 
from the fatal malady the congressman said his wife believed it 
wrong for her brother to go public with his rebuttal of her 
assertions 
she thinks doug owes her an apology for going to the press 
instead of her dornan said 
dornan seeking reelection to a third term in congress said 
the description stemmed from his wifes worries about her brother 
and from pictures she had seen of aids victims 
shed been worrying and it came out as a reality instead of a 
fear thats the one mistake sallie made dornan said 
sallie is just a walking heart dornan said i think she 
had imagined this so often she thought she had seen them 
hansen later called reporters to deny he had aids though he has 
friends who are homosexual he said he belives the gay lifestyle 
is wrong 
hansen tested negative for the aids virus in a test arranged by 
the los angeles times 
hansen said he hadnt seen his sister since their mothers 
funeral in 1983 and dornan said he has seen hansen only once in 30 
years 
