<TEXT>
now that such former best sellers as stocks and 
mutual funds have fallen out of favor financial institutions are 
busy these days pushing a hot new idea certificates of deposit 
not just plain vanilla cds mind you though you can certainly 
still get those stodgy oldtimers if you want them 
what were dealing with now are risingrate cds floatingrate 
cds cds with no set maturity dates even cds that effectively let 
you make a legal bet on your favorite sports team or the outcome of 
the november election 
all this hasnt happened just by chance the stock market crash 
last fall and the wide swings in interest rates over the past 
several years have brought big changes in the marketplace where 
brokers and bankers sell their merchandise 
i choose to think of it as a rebirth of investor prudence 
says william brennan a valley forge pa adviser on tax and 
investment planning 
todays low tax rates and market turmoil have reinstated 
preservation of principal as a justifiable objective for personal 
planning 
in this environment cds are a natural choice for financial 
marketers to seize upon thanks to todays high level of real 
interest rates as compared with the inflation rate they can 
offer a reasonable return with the backing of federal deposit 
insurance 
and thanks to financial deregulation the oncerigid format of a 
certificate of deposit has become very flexible 
in general financial advisers say that is a plus for savers 
and investors but they caution that it takes a lot of care to 
distinguish the substance from the sizzle in the new generation of 
cds 
there is no real harm for instance in buying a cd whose yield 
will vary depending on the outcome of the super bowl or the 
election as long as you have enough financial leeway to play that 
kind of game with your money 
a little nononsense calculation may cool your enthusiasm for 
such a deal which dont really offer much of a payout or loss 
with one presidential cd now on the market the newsletter 
100 highest yield calculates if the candidate of your choice wins 
with 59 percent of the popular vote the amount president reagan 
got in his 1984 landslide you would receive an extra 1013 over 
the next four years on a 1000 deposit 
if you opt to shop purely for yield and safety the choices are 
still bewilderingly large 
newsletters like 100 highest yields in north palm beach fla 
and income amp safety in fort lauderdale fla compile lists of 
topyielding cd offerings by banks and savings institutions around 
the country 
even with federal deposit insurance it makes sense these days 
to check out the status and prospects of some faraway institution 
before you mail off a large deposit check 
alternatively you can do your cd shopping at brokerage firms 
which may have certificates from a wide variety of insured 
institutions to offer 
brokerage houses not only seek out the highestpaying 
institutions to provide cds for their customers but they also 
frequently negotiate special package deals that lead to higher 
rates than the same banks offer directly to the public says the 
income amp safety newsletter 
it may be possible to liquidate a cd investment bought from a 
broker before maturity without paying a penalty since most brokers 
endeavor to maintain a continuous secondary market in the cds 
they sell 
you probably wont have to pay a commission when you buy or 
sell but if you are thinking of selling before maturity check 
into the spread the difference between the brokers bid and 
asked prices 
just possibly the spread might be as large as or larger than 
the early withdrawal penalty 
