<TEXT>
eastern airlines on wednesday announced the recall 
of 300 furloughed flight attendants which follows the recent 
layoffs of more than 3000 employees to streamline the moneylosing 
carriers operations 
the furloughed flight attendants are being recalled effective 
oct 21 because of the popularity of a longterm leave of absence 
program said eastern spokesman robin matell 
the program was offered as a way of minimizing the impact of 
furloughs and more volunteers were attracted than had been 
anticipated matell said more than 500 flight attendants took the 
leave offer 
now 300 fired flight attendants will be recalled on the basis of 
seniority matell said 
last week a federal appeals court in washington struck down a 
lower court judge who had barred eastern from carrying out the 
furloughs the us circuit court of appeals rejected the unions 
contention that the layoffs were part of a unionbusting campaign 
by easterns parent texas air corp and its chairman frank lorenzo 
along with the furloughs which took effect sept 10 and 
represented easterns largest layoff plans in its 60year history 
the carrier eliminated service to 14 cities and closed its kansas 
city hub 
easterns recall coincides with a seasonal increase in flights 
to core markets along the east coast and into the caribbean and 
latin america 
matell said additional employees also may be recalled 
we have to evaluate staffing needs and determine whats 
what he said 
