before a hearing in delaware chancery court over the groups 
attempt to wage a proxy battle to pressure the company into putting 
itself up for sale 
just 20 minutes into the hearing zenith also surrendered on the 
issue at stake in the proceeding whether brookhursts proxy 
solicitation would trigger zeniths poison pill takeover 
defense 
stephen herrmann zeniths attorney declared that the consent 
solicitation of sept 14 would not trigger the rights plan even if 
15 percent of the shareholders proxies were obtained by brookhurst 
partners 
this means brookhurst is now free to solicit shareholder support 
in its efforts to replace some company directors and sell zenith 
brookhurst which owns 61 percent of zeniths stock is 
proposing to reduce the board from 10 members to six and replace 
three of the six with its own candidates 
zenith the only remaining us television maker is 
incorporated in delaware but based in glenview ill north of 
chicago 
the company has indicated its desire to remain independent and 
until wednesday had resisted giving the shareholder list to 
brookhurst 
